Interface DynamicContainer<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Item
    All Superinterfaces:
    Container, fr.cnrs.iees.identity.Identity, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Resettable

    public interface DynamicContainer<T>
extends Container
    An interface for containers which must delay addition and deletion of items up to a given step
    Author:
    Jacques Gignoux - 24 janv. 2020

    • Method Detail

      • addItem

        void addItem​(T item)
        Tag an item for addition into this container's item list. The item will be effectively added only when effectChanges() or effectAllChanges() is called thereafter. This enables one to keep the container state consistent over time in discrete time simulations.
        Parameters:
        item - the item to add

      • removeItem

        void removeItem​(T item)
        Tag an item for removal from this container's item list. The item will be effectively removed only when effectChanges() or effectAllChanges() is called thereafter. This enables one to keep the container state consistent over time in discrete time simulations.
        Parameters:
        item - the item to remove

      • effectChanges

        void effectChanges​(java.util.Collection<T>... changedLists)
        Effectively remove and add items from the container lists (before a call to this method, they are just stored into itemsToRemove and itemsToAdd). NB: to recursively effect changes for all sub-containers, use effectAllChanges(). The arguments are here in case a return list of items is needed - depends on context of course

      • structureChanged

        boolean structureChanged()
        Flag used to signal if the container has been changed during a computation step
        Returns:
        true if changed since last effectChanges()

      • changeStructure

        DynamicContainer<T> changeStructure()
        Sets the changed flag to true

        default boolean stateChanged()
